% ================= Chapter 1 =================
\chapter{Introduction}

\section{Purpose}

\subsection{Purpose of the SRS}
The basic purpose of the Software Requirement Specification is to show the complete visual picture of the Fair and Unbiased Assessment System. It describes the system specifications and functional requirements so stakeholders, developers, and testers clearly understand system behavior and expectations.

\subsection{Intended Audience}
This SRS is intended for stakeholders, developers, testers, and end users.

\section{Stakeholders}

\textbf{Institutional Decision Makers:} Ensure educational compliance and fairness.  

\textbf{Project Managers:} Monitor progress and resources.

\section{Development Teams}

\textbf{Software Engineers:} Implement system requirements.  

\textbf{System Architects:} Design scalable and fault-tolerant architecture.

\section{Testers}

\textbf{Quality Assurance Specialists:} Validate system correctness and fairness.

\section{End Users}

\textbf{Assessors and Candidates:} Use the system for fair assessments.

% ================= Scope =================
\section{Scope}

\subsection{Software Product Identification}
The software is named \textbf{Fair and Unbiased Assessment System (FUAS)}.
\begin{itemize}
\item Registration and authentication
\item Evaluation and scoring
\item Report generation
\item Content management
\item System administration
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Product Functions}
\begin{itemize}
\item User verification
\item Course assignment
\item Upload quizzes and tests
\item Automated evaluation
\item Report generation
\item Data security
\end{itemize}

The system will not:
\begin{itemize}
\item Generate answer keys automatically
\item Modify uploaded assessments
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Application Description}
The system ensures unbiased evaluation of quizzes, assignments, and tests in educational institutions.

\subsection{Benefits, Objectives, and Goals}
\begin{itemize}
\item Bias reduction
\item Transparency
\item 99\% scoring accuracy
\item Support up to 10,000 users
\item Secure encrypted data
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Consistency with Higher-Level Specifications}
Aligned with institutional and regulatory standards.

